cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the application of deep convolutional neural networks for detecting interstitial lung disease patterns from computed tomography (CT) scans. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of Fisher vector encoding for deep feature encoding, which is a technique commonly used in multimedia analysis (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper involves statistical analysis and cross-validation techniques, which are relevant to the field of machine learning and statistics (cs.MS).
